Xuwen&#xd;
Is a young professional in the fields cultural diplomacy and intergration. As a member of the EU-China Friendship Program, she has supported and promoted cooperation between China and Europe. Furthermore, after completing her Master of Creative Culture at the German Institute of Cultural Diplomacy, she participated in the European Union's creative culture and cultural heritage research project. She is committed to promoting creativity, intergration and the exploration and development of the cultural industry.&#xd;
&#xd;
Li jiashan&#xd;
As a Professor at the Beijing Second Foreign Language University, Li jiashan is an expert in the field of creative culture in China. She is most notably known for her role as the  founder of several cultural organization, that are dedicated to promoting understanding and cooperation between the EU and China. These organization are the  National Creative Culture Research Platform, the Central and Eastern European Creative Culture Forum. &#xd;
&#xd;
Olivia Lewis&#xd;
Is a bilingual, resourceful and above all highly adaptable young professional in the fields International Relations, Public Affairs and European Public Policy. With 7 years of highly advanced study in 4 different countries including the USA, Germany, The Netherlands, and Denmark, she has successfully obtained a Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from the University of Rochester and a Masters in Public Policy from the Willy Brandt School of Public Policy in Germany.  With 3.5 years of experience in both the legal and political fields, Olivia has proven herself to be  detail-oriented and dedicated with strong leadership skills and organisational leadership strategies.  &#xd;
&#xd;
Atman-one&#xd;
As well as being  a Chinese contemporary artist, Atman-ones holds a Professorship at the Department of Art at Donghua University in Shanghai..Atman-one is committed to the development of activities in the field of cross-border art. He has been a receipent of the Italian Florence Biennale Award and has successfully represented Chinese artists at the UN Art Exhibition in New York. &#xd;
&#xd;
Tuergeng.Tuexun&#xd;
&#xd;
Tuergeng.Tuexun is an outstanding artist. After completing his Masters degree in Art History at the University of Bologna, Italy, he has been devoted to art education in art theory research. He has served as a liaison officer at the Italian Venice Art Festival  and has planned and executed a Sino-European contemporary art exhibition.&#xd;
&#xd;
Lisa Ma&#xd;
Lisa Ma is a passionate professional with robust experience in planning and organizing events, exhibitions and fundraising projects, as well as providing support to executive-level staff. She was previously a Research Intern at the China Institute in New York City. Furthermore she acted as a representative of the non-governmental organization (UN ECOSOC) in Shanghai and a specialist on the cultural exchange between China and America.  She completed her undergraduate degrees in Art History and Social Psychology at Sarah Lawrence College. &#xd;
As a I-lingual recent graduate with the multicultural perspective Yao Ma is ready to bring strong communication skills, dynamic background, and education to a growing organization.
